TOM--- Best thing to do concerning your 62 (below) is to talk with the guys who 
would be doing the picking-up.  If you have two rolling wheels for them, they 
can use an old-technology wrecker; with flat tires they can use a dolly.

I had the easiest time as your last responder suggested -- cutting up the 
vehicle with a Sawzall or maybe putting an abrasive disk in a circular saw.  
Then you can take the bits to a scrapyard at your leisure.  Don't be tempted to 
trade for something there.  I picked up an old mailbox, thinking it would make 
a good place to store charcoal and barbecue tools -- the wife hated it ;-))

Since this is Friday and you are in Baltimore:  I am looking for good, solid 
metal just below the windshield for my '69 Bay.  If you have this, and would 
like to sell same to me, I'm interested.... thanks.  Possibly I could help with 
the scrapping process.  I am in the Queenstown, MD phone book.   Good luck,  
Glenn McComas

